1. *Tvoga* oca sam sreo na ulici. (*Your* father, I met on the street.)
2. Ne znam gde je *tvoga*. (I don't know where *yours* is.)
3. Uzmite ovaj poklon za *tvoga* brata. (Take this gift for *your* brother.)
4. *Tvoga* psa sam video u parku. (I saw *your* dog in the park.)
5. Ovo je kuća *tvoga* dede. (This is the house of *your* grandfather.)
6. Nadam se da ćeš doći sa *tvoga* putovanja. (I hope you will come back from *your* trip.)
7. *Tvoga* sina sam video juče na ulici. (I saw *your* son on the street yesterday.)
8. Zamolio bih te da mi pozajmiš jednu od *tvoga* knjiga. (I would ask you to lend me one of *your* books.)
9. Pogledaj u fioku *tvoga* stola. (Look in the drawer of *your* desk.)
10. Koliko si potrošio novca sa *tvoga* računa? (How much money have you spent from *your* account?)

Note: In Serbian, the word "tvoga" means "your" and it is a possessive pronoun that agrees with the gender and number of the noun it modifies.